Description:
Promise and Potential in the Heart of Coburg!
On a substantial block of land complete with ROW at the rear, this freestanding period home provides an environment of immediate comfort along with outstanding opportunities for those looking to revive or renew (STCA). Immaculately presented throughout, the home's current accommodation includes two large bedrooms (one with BIRs) and neat central bathroom, front lounge and adjoining dining room, separate kitchen/meals. Features include a gas heater and air conditioner (in the lounge), high ceilings, polished floorboards, plus a wonderfully deep backyard with bungalow/studio, garage, shed and plenty of room to expand. A sensational location, the best of Coburg is at your fingertips including trains, trams and buses, renowned shops and major supermarkets, cafes and restaurants, easy access to local parks and schools - and all just 10kms from the city. First time offered in over 60 years - what an opportunity!
Land Size: 538sqm Approx
Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
Insights: 17 Hudson Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 58 other 2 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
The Charm of 'Serendipity'
From the enticing façade through to its sympathetically renovated interior, this dignified five bedroom two bathroom Edwardian delivers expansive family living. A leadlight entrance hall, lofty ornate ceilings, picture rails and four superb OFP's speak of craftsmanship and adorn four bedrooms before giving way to a spacious open plan, seamlessly integrating modern living with the charismatic charm of yesteryear. A granite topped kitchen boasting 800mm Lofra range and Miele dishwasher oversees this area, showcasing elegant built-in cabinetry, gas log fire and bay window offering views of established gardens. Upstairs an attic styled retreat provides additional living and presents a further bedroom. Boasting abundant storage, heating/cooling, OSP, solar panels, shed/workshop, moments to bustling Sydney Road cafes, trams, schools and parks, inspection will impress.

Description:
Inner City, Designer living at Its Finest!
A stunning example of new age inner-city living, this brand new townhouses delivers modern day comfort and convenience.
Cleverly designed to promote low maintenance living, the ground floor comprising a main bedroom with ensuite & B.I.R, laundry and internal access via a single lock-up garage. Heading upstairs, you're greeted by the large open living area, complete with gorgeous hardwood floors underfoot, the gourmet kitchen with Caesarstone bench tops designer tapware and Bosch stainless steel appliances. You'll also find the generous sized second bedroom, designer bathroom and entertainer's balcony. Split system heating and cooling in every room and camera intercom further add to the property's appeal which is superbly placed in the heart of Coburg, within walking distance to Coburg Train Station, Sydney Road shopping precinct, cafes and schools.

Description:
A recreational family lifestyle with luxurious dimensions
Contemporary design, lustrous finishes and luxurious amenity overflow in this newly-renovated four-bedroom residence, situated on a vast and peaceful corner allotment amid the beautiful parklands of the prestigious Pentridge Village estate. As the new heart of Coburg, Pentridge Village will soon enjoy a new retail arcade of boutique shopping, tasty cafés, and state-of-the-art cinemas, which together with its position so close to Merri Creek trails, the Doug Hull Adventure Park, and bustling Sydney Road’s shopping, cafés and transport, provides the perfect environment for growing families.
Welcomed by the flow of stylish European Oak flooring, the home’s new sassiness is abundant through a well-proportioned four-bedroom, two-bathroom layout. Two zoned living spaces cater to private family entertainment, including an open plan living and entertaining area spilling into a sundrenched alfresco courtyard and landscaped garden, and a private family upstairs retreat for relaxation and study. Embracing luxury for daily living, a stunning kitchen with glass splashbacks is fully-appointed including new Bosch cooking appliances. Two sumptuously modern bathrooms and a guest powder room with Belgium stone tiling provide amenity to four spacious robed bedrooms, including an oversized master suite with sunroom, walk-in robe and ensuite, and a ground floor guest suite or home office.
Cocooned in comfort, enjoy ducted heating, upstairs split system air-conditioning, and LED lighting throughout, and finished with a large laundry and remote double garage with internal access.
Only 8kms from the CBD, enjoy easy family living with all the perks of vibrant Coburg at your doorstep including parks and recreation, shopping and daily conveniences surrounding, and an easy CBD commute via Coburg Station, Nicholson Street and Sydney Road trams, a short walk to Coburg Primary and Coburg High schools, and easy access to Coburg Homemaker Centre and more.
Insights: 1 Farm Road, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 49 other 4 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Abundant Advantages
In a family friendly position moments to a wide range of amenities, this welcoming three bedroom home offers abundant advantages and outstanding options. Situated on 2 lots totalling approximately 457m2 in a tree lined street, it's impeccably neat, immediately inviting and amenable to a myriad of future options including renovating, extending or transforming the site with something entirely new (subject to council approval). Presenting a living room with gas log fire and decorative ceiling detail, kitchen/meals, covered entertainer's deck and plenty of outdoor space, the home is enhanced by polished floorboards, new carpets, an open fireplace, ducted cooling and a freshly painted interior.
An Electrolux gas stove, tiled splashbacks, cupboards and great preparation space make the kitchen ready to cook delicious dishes, and passionate cooks could easily enhance to their taste. Three sizeable bedrooms include one with a large built-in robe, and the central bathroom hosts a shower, bath, toilet and vanity. Complete with a laundry, large storage cupboards, long side driveway, generous garage and rear ROW, it's got more than just the basics in place. A stroll to transport, Coburg North Primary, Harmony Park, Coburg North Village, O'Heas Bakery and Coburg Tennis Club, this opportunity will find fans.

Ready to be returned to former glory, the residence displays classic period appeal with ceilings that reach to over three metres in height! With everything in place for a brilliant makeover it will be a breeze to rejuvenate and capitalise on the existing charm of this delightful home.

Description:
The Endless Charm of Living Parkside
Situated in the tightest held pocket of East Coburg this three bedroom Californian Bungalow home is surrounded by tranquillity, quality heritage homes and spacious allotments.
From a charismatic facade to an outstanding interior and outdoor entertainer's nirvana, this outstanding home delivers exceptional family living. A meticulous renovation celebrates the period pedigree of the home while delivering the expansive indoor-outdoor living domains that suit a modern lifestyle.
Picture perfect, nestled in a heritage-styled front garden, you are welcomed by a leadlight adorned door to an entrance hall featuring high decorative ceilings and delicate fretwork before introducing expansive open plan living.
Stunning Blackbutt hardwood timber floors line this light filled domain that flows to an entertainer's deck and oversees a professionally designed and landscaped deep garden allotment for a seamless indoor-outdoor lifestyle.
An outstanding Shaker style kitchen with timber island, impressive 900mm range, dishwasher and endless storage highlight this exceptional home.
Grand bedrooms one with bay window and open fireplace, two with quality timber robes share a central bathroom with elegant timber panel detail and pedestal basin, while a separate laundry, second toilet, hydronic heating and OSP assure comfort and convenience.
In a prized family street where at one end kookaburras herald the scenic Merri Creek parklands and the other offers the convenience of the No. 1 tram you could not be better placed.
Surrounded by a choice of schools, buses, Coburg Station and the cosmopolitan delights of bustling Sydney Road, inspection is a must.
Insights: 6 Merribell Avenue, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Other features include gas heater and air conditioner (both in the lounge), full-size laundry, private garden surrounds and rear access into the remote-control garage. South of Bell Street in one of Coburg's favourite pockets, it's close to Melville Road trams and Coburg Station, popular schools, shops and supermarkets, as well as Sydney Road cafes and restaurants. An ideal first home, easy investment or value-packed downsize option! Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Setting A Superb Standard
A haven of tranquillity, this tastefully renovated, light-filled home on a 371m2 allotment (approx) enjoys a premium position just a short walk from the bus, station, local shops, tram and the home-maker centre.
Offering an enticing city fringe lifestyle, an utterly charming façade gives way to a perfectly presented interior introducing a large living room with built in cabinetry for books and audio-visual equipment, which flows through to a casual living meals including a Blanco equipped kitchen with striking timber bench tops and a study nook.
Three bedrooms are served by a luxury updated bathroom featuring an oversize shower and contemporary wall hung basin, complemented by a very handy second toilet off the laundry. The private rear yard is home to a choice of covered and open alfresco areas, a shed, raised vegie beds and lawn for the kids and their pets.
Classic offerings of leadlight, fretwork, high ceilings, picture rails, roses, cornice and open fire-places combine with contemporary conveniences of ducted heating and cooling, split system and off street parking - it's a clear winner.
